Subject: NULling OS/2 Commands in a REXX .CMD

>I am executing an OS/2 Warp COPY command in a REXX .CMD.  I want to format
>all output from the procedure.  I cannot seem to stop the COPY command from
>displaying to the screen, even though I have tracing turned off.  I am
>executing
>the following:
>
>   'COPY F:\FX\NEWUSER\*.* F:\FX\'USERID '>NUL'
>
>Userid is just a variable that represents a directory name.  Any ideas?

Try this:
   'COPY F:\FX\NEWUSER\*.* F:\FX\'USERID '>NUL 2>NUL'


