In article <43ccjc$lp3@coranto.ucs.mun.ca>, misnlhyd@nlnet.nf.ca writes:
> I am executing an OS/2 Warp COPY command in a REXX .CMD.  I want to format all
> output from the procedure.  I cannot seem to stop the COPY command from
> displaying to the screen, even though I have tracing turned off.  I am executing
> the following:
>
>    'COPY F:\FX\NEWUSER\*.* F:\FX\'USERID '>NUL'

You need to redirect stderr to NUL, not just stdout.
Stderr is referred to by 2>.  so add 2>NUL to the above.
Or, add "2>&1" to the redirect stderr to the same place
as stdout.


